      • hashtable

        public static <K,V> MapBuilder<K,V,Hashtable<K,V>> hashtable()
        Creates a new builder populating a Hashtable. Note that if you just want a synchronized map, you can use the following: 
         
 MapBuilder.<Long, Long>hash().in(Collections::synchronizedMap).put(134, 632634)
        This is provided primarily for compatibility with legacy code.
        Type Parameters:
        K - Ye key type
        V - Ye value type
        Returns:
        Aye builder
        See Also:
        Collections.synchronizedMap(java.util.Map<K, V>)

      • in

        public <N extends Map<K,V>> MapBuilder<K,V,N> in(Function<M,N> wrapper)
        Returns a new builder populating a map which is the result of applying the given function to the existing map. Usage: 
         
 MapBuilder.<String, String>hash().put("a","a").in(Collections::unmodifiableMap)
        Note that this may change whether further mutations are supported.
        Type Parameters:
        N - The new map type
        Parameters:
        wrapper - The wrapping or transforming function
